parameters:
Mage Relm: The depths of the Arros Cave... it resembles an
ancient ruins, doesn't it?

Girl Ect: It seems like Papa was thinking that it's highly
likely to be ruins from the same era.

Girl Ect: It might be a place related to the ancient kingdom
of Basileia.
Thief Nora: Is there another strange thing here...?

Priestess Sophia: It seems like we were attacked by moving
statues, hehe. It might be hard to believe.

Girl Ect: Amazing! I want to see it! Let's go deeper
quickly!

Clea: I'm not sure what will happen, but I would like you to
wait here if possible.

Girl Ect: Hehehe, that's not possible! Papa said that people
who stop with the words he said are not adventurers!

Clea: ...I understand. Please make sure to stay close to me,
okay?

Girl Ect: Of course! Hehe, today I'll be protected by Clea-
san!

Thief Nora: Y-Yes, I knew it! Just like before, they'll
definitely come attacking!

Mage Relm: Please don't raise your voice! They might react
to our voices!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, I wonder if Relm-chan won't react
to loud voices for now?
Clea: Is there something bothering you?

Young girl Ect: Goddess, humans, dragons... According to
Papa's prediction, this place might have been an ancient
training ground.

Young girl Ect: Those recognized by the goddess can fight
dragons... In other words, they have the right to battle
demons.

Mage Relm: It's quite similar to the legendary hero tale,
isn't it? However, the Kingdom of Basileia is before the
appearance of the hero, right?

Young girl Ect: Yes, that's it! If that's the case, I wonder
if Papa's prediction was wrong...?
Clea: We came here to confirm that... right?
Young girl Ect: Of course! Now, let's move forward--
Thief Nora: Y-Yes, they're moving after all!
Clea: Please step back, it's going to be a battle.

Young girl Ect: Amazing, amazing, amazing! It's really
moving! Let's take it home!

Mage Relm: Sigh... She's quite an extraordinary girl, isn't
she?

Clea: Please confirm if we can take it home after the
battle.
Young girl Ect: It's all falling apart... Huh?

Young girl Ect: Is this the power source of the goddess
statue? It's different from the crystal... It feels more
like a gem.
Clea: Please take it back and study it.

Young girl Ect: Yes! I need to investigate my father's
research again...
Clea: Let's proceed to the very end.

Mage Relm: We're moving to the entrance... This is exactly
the same as the previous ruins, isn't it?
Young girl Ect: Is it easy to move this magic circle?

Mage Relm: No way! It's something that can really only be
achieved in a limited area!

Mage Relm: If we can achieve this magic circle, becoming a
high-level mage is definitely within reach.

Young girl Ect: I've made up my mind...! Now, let's hurry
back to the Adventurer's Guild!

Stolge of Affection: This Lachio Ruins is still an
unexplored place.

Stolge of Affection: I would like to know Ect's current
thoughts on showing her knowledge of excavation and ruins
here.
Young girl Ect: I have the same thoughts as my father.

Young girl Ect: This ruins is a place related to the
mythical kingdom of Basileia that appears in legends.

Young girl Ect: I believe this place was like a training
ground to create warriors who fight against demons.

Young girl Ect: However, up until now, it's just a
hypothesis based on visible information, just like my
father.

Young girl Ect: I want to actually go inside and thoroughly
investigate the structure of the ruins and the motifs
depicted on the walls--

Stolge of Affection (It's like the reincarnation of Melos...
Passion, knowledge, and overwhelming curiosity)

Stolge of Affection (Melos, there's no doubt... this child
is your daughter)

Young girl Ect: The common points with other ruins existing
in Fotizona--

Stolge of Affection: I understand, I understand, it's okay
now! If we go any further, it will get dark. There's no
problem here.

Clea: I think she has an incredible amount of knowledge. It
felt like I was talking to Melos-san.
Young girl Ect: Ehehe, I did it...!

Stolge of Affection: Let's go back to the Adventurer's Guild
and request the final test from Agonia.
Young female explorer Ect: Hmm... I still don't understand.

Young female explorer Ect: The gem I found here before also
just looks like an ordinary gem...

Young female explorer Ect: I guess I have no choice but to
ask Relm, who is a member of the Magic Academy...
Young female explorer Ect: Who's there!?
Fake adventurer Psema: No need to be on guard, miss.

Fake adventurer Psema: I came to meet you because I have
something to tell you about your missing father.
